<div class="results-text">
  <p>This tax charge was introduced on 7 January 2013.</p>

  <h4>How and when to pay</h4>

  <p>You will have to pay back the tax you owe through Self Assessment. You’ll need to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/self-assessment-tax-returns">Self Assessment</a> by 5 October 2014, and complete your Self Assessment tax return in time.</p>

  <h4>What happens next</h4>
  
  <p>You’ll need to pay back any tax you owe through <a href="https://www.gov.uk/self-assessment-tax-returns">self assessment</a>. You can either:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li>carry on getting Child Benefit for the year</li>
    <li><a href="http://hmrc.gov.uk/childbenefitcharge/stopchbpayments.htm" rel="external">stop getting Child Benefit</a></li>
  </ul>  
  
  <% if @calculator.amount_owed > 0 && @calculator.starting_children.any? %>

    <h4>New children</h4>

    <p>From now, you can either:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>carry on getting Child Benefit for the year, and pay whatever you owe back as tax</li>
      <li>register the child for Child Benefit and ask for it not to be paid to you</li>
    </ul>

  <% end %>

</div>
